      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Although this may make sense when we only support a limited number of filters, it won\u0027t scale when we have more. I don\u0027t think it adds a lot of value than the current implementation (you need to type in just one character to invoke the auto-complete dropdown). I\u0027ll add a link to explain the query syntax in a future CL.\n\nI think what I am concerning about is not that the users need to type one character, but about how would they know if we do *not* support a filter. They need to type a character to trigger the auto suggest, but the auto suggest will be based on the character that they type.\n\nBut I agree that this is probably not a big deal though. I saw you created a bug for adding instructions of the search bar. I think it\u0027s good enough,",
